  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I transfer my whatsapp chats from Android to iOS?",
  "response": "Transferring WhatsApp chats from Android to iOS can be done using the built-in feature provided by WhatsApp. Here are the steps to follow:\n\n### Requirements:\n1. **iPhone running iOS 15.5 or newer**\n2. **Android device running Android 5 or newer**\n3. **Latest version of WhatsApp installed on both devices**\n4. **Same phone number on both devices**\n5. **Both devices connected to the same Wi-Fi network**\n6. **Use the same WhatsApp account on both devices**\n\n### Steps:\n\n1. **Prepare the iPhone:**\n   - On your new iPhone, download and install the \"Move to iOS\" app from the Google Play Store on your Android device.\n\n2. **Set up the iPhone:**\n   - Begin the initial setup of your iPhone. When you reach the \"Apps & Data\" screen, choose \"Move Data from Android.\"\n\n3. **Connect to \"Move to iOS\" app:**\n   - Open the \"Move to iOS\" app on your Android device and follow the instructions. You will receive a code on your iPhone. Enter this code on your Android device to establish a connection.\n\n4. **Transfer Data:**\n   - On your Android device, select \"WhatsApp\" as the data you want to transfer. The \"Move to iOS\" app will prepare the data for transfer.\n\n5. **Complete the Transfer:**\n   - Wait for the transfer process to complete. Once done, continue setting up your iPhone.\n\n6. **Install WhatsApp on iPhone:**\n   - Download and install WhatsApp on your iPhone from the App Store.\n\n7. **Activate WhatsApp on iPhone:**\n   - Open WhatsApp on your iPhone and sign in using the same phone number you used on your Android device.\n\n8. **Import Chat History:**\n   - After verifying your phone number, WhatsApp will prompt you to import the chat history. Follow the on-screen instructions to complete the import.\n\n### Additional Notes:\n- Ensure both devices are connected to power during the transfer process to avoid interruptions.\n- The transfer process may take some time, depending on the amount of data being transferred.\n\nUsing these steps, you should be able to transfer your WhatsApp chats from Android to iOS seamlessly.",
